# ReeveOS Homepage — Cursor Rules

## Project
Single-page marketing homepage for ReeveOS (reeveos.app) — a zero-commission booking, ordering, and business management platform for UK independent businesses.

## Tech Stack
- Vite + React (JSX, not TypeScript)
- Tailwind CSS v3
- Framer Motion for animations
- Single page, no routing needed
- Deploy target: Vercel

## Brand Tokens — LOCKED, NO EXCEPTIONS

### Colours
- Rich Black: #111111 (50% dominant — backgrounds, nav, footer)
- Dark Surface: #181818 (card backgrounds, alternating sections)
- Gold: #C9A84C (15% accent — CTAs, labels, highlights, borders)
- Warm White: #FAFAF8 (30% — body text, headings)
- Mid Grey: #999999 (muted text, sublines)
- Border: #222222 (subtle dividers, card borders)

### Typography
- Font: Figtree ONLY — no other fonts, ever
- Load from Google Fonts: weights 300, 400, 500, 600, 700, 800
- Headlines: weight 800, letter-spacing -0.035em
- Body: weight 400, line-height 1.7
- UI/Buttons: weight 600-700
- Labels: weight 600, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.15em, font-size 12px

### UI Details
- Card border-radius: 16-20px
- Button border-radius: 10-12px
- Pill badges: border-radius 100px
- Section spacing: 100px+ vertical padding
- Minimal shadows, prefer border + subtle glow for elevation
- Gold-bordered cards for emphasis (1px solid rgba(201,168,76,0.3))

## Design Source
The exact Figma design data is available in this repo:
- `figma-design-tree.txt` — Full layer tree with colours, fonts, sizes, text, layout modes, borders, radii
- `figma-image-urls.json` — Signed URLs for all images used in the design
- `figma-raw.json` — Complete Figma API response (if fetched)

To refresh from Figma: `node fetch-figma.js` (requires FIGMA_TOKEN in .env)

ALWAYS read `figma-design-tree.txt` before making any changes. Match the exact:
- Colours (hex values from bg: fields)
- Font sizes (from font: fields, e.g. font:Figtree/400/48.0px)
- Dimensions (from [width×height] brackets)
- Text content (from quoted strings)
- Border colours and radii
- Layout directions and spacing (from flex: and pad: fields)

Do NOT guess. Every value is in the tree file.

## Figma Link
https://www.figma.com/design/V4v1EQKpNiZfKxobV1l5en/UX-Pilot--AI-UI-Generator---AI-Wireframe-Generator--Community-?node-id=1-5&t=fxTsr8HWHlHEg9Yw-1

## Section Structure (11 sections)
1. Sticky Nav — Gold R mark + white wordmark, transparent → dark on scroll
2. Hero — Rotating headline word (restaurant/barber/café/etc), two CTAs
3. Social Proof Bar — Stats strip
4. The Problem — Commission comparison cards
5. Features — 3x3 grid with real photos
6. Business Types — Horizontal scroll cards (6 verticals)
7. Dashboard Preview — Browser-frame mockup
8. Testimonials — Three quote cards
9. Pricing — Free / Growth £29 / Scale £59
10. Gold CTA — Only section with gold background
11. Footer — Four columns, Gold R mark

## Image Strategy
- Use high-quality Unsplash images for all photography
- British high street, real businesses, warm natural light
- Each feature card and business type card needs a relevant image
- Hero: British high street at golden hour OR business montage

## Key Rules
1. Figtree ONLY — never use any other font
2. Dark-first — Rich Black dominant, Gold is accent not primary
3. Responsive — mobile-first, works perfectly on all screen sizes
4. Real images — use Unsplash URLs, never grey placeholders
5. British spelling — colours not colors, organisation not organization
6. Premium feel — must look like a £100k brand, Stripe-quality polish
7. All animations subtle — no bouncing, no excessive movement

## Pricing Data
- Free: £0/mo, 1 staff login, 100 bookings/mo, basic listing
- Growth: £29/mo (MOST POPULAR), 5 staff, deposits, CRM, marketing tools
- Scale: £59/mo, unlimited staff, floor plan, white-label, priority support
- All plans: 0% commission, card processing from 0.3% via Dojo

